The paper discusses algorithms for genome-wide association studies, which involve analyzing large amounts of genetic data to identify associations with various traits. This falls under the field of computational genetics, which is closely related to machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computational Geometry and Topology), which includes topics such as computational biology and bioinformatics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which all involve the analysis of large datasets and the development of algorithms for data processing and analysis.
